<br>
Some areas I noticed:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  &quot;For those who choose to cancel their subscription to the Legends service, characters will be able to return to the server from which they came. &quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
There you go, the only cold hard statement VI made in that paragraph.  Characters <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Will Be</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> transfered back to their old servres no matter what server they came from.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  &quot;To limit possible abuse, we reserve the right to impose a 6 month wait period between cancellation moves for the same account (or accounts owned by the same person).&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
What the hell is that? &quot;we <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  reserve</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the right&quot;?  reserve means they have the right, but whether they use the right or not is entirely up to them.  Gray area number 1.<br>
And what is this &quot;6 months wait period&quot;?  does that mean that there is a 6 months delay between the day of cancelation to the day of move?  or does it mean that your character would return to their old server after 6 months since you subscribed the legend service?  Gray area number 2.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  &quot;Possession of excessive amounts of coin&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Define &quot;excessive&quot;.  In our server anybody with 10K is mega rich while it's like middle class wealth in some other servers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  &quot;Possession of excessive amounts of saleable items&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
How many can you have anyways?  every character has limited bank and inventory spaces.  Again, define &quot;excessive&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  &quot;Abuse of the Legends Service - attempting to transfer items from one server to another, which could also lead to disciplinary action taken on the account&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Now this one I like.  This sort of &quot;abuse&quot; isn't like bug exploitation or hacking.  This is entirely subjective and any number of people can come up with different ideas on what defines &quot;abuse&quot; in this case.  VI is a money making company, therefore they would not want to piss off their customers too much.  To me, this line is just complete BS.<br>
<br>
<br>
LOL...oh, man....this is getting much like a rant..i've been spending way too much time in the soapbox. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
